Two-way bindings
are a powerful mechanism to implement bi-directional flow of data. In this release, we've extended our implementation
so that they can be used on struct fields:

Python is a dynamically typed programming language, where type hints can be added and checked with additional tools such as mypy or ty. In this release, we've added type hinting for Python to the slint compiler. This also comes
with a more convenient way of loading .slint files in Python:

Import the file in your Python code to load and access the Slint UI and get coverage for Python static type checkers,
such as mypy or ty.

